spans.text: No more my heart to vainer hopes I give , But live for thee , whose bounty bids me live
all that bears the name of joy
thy sacred ray Shine over my heart
my heart , to other interests true , A moment balance betwixt the world and you
the pleasures of the world lay
the period of their power and pride
If he that loved me knew no other love
OH change your false desires , you flattering train
spare the tribute of a female tear
yield one tender moment to deplore Those gentle hearts that I must hold no more
Those gentle hearts that I must hold no more
